flowRoot.flowPara: Recipe to compute the enlarged corner:
1- Compute the center of the smoothed corner S
2- Get the line equation of SC
3- Get the coordiantes of F, center of the enlarged corner
5.1- Compute K, the intersection of (HI) and the arc (ABC)
5.2- If the intersection is between [HI], skip 5.3
5.3- Compute M, the intersection of the enlarged circle and the arc (ABC)
6.1- Compute L, the intersection of (GJ) and the arc (CDE)
6.2- If the intersection is between [GJ], skip 6.3
6.3- Compute N, the intersection of the enlarged circle and the arc (CDE)
To enlarge, we have two ideas:
1- follow the line going from the gorner angle to the center of the smoothed circle
2- follow a cricle, which center is the middle of the centers of the two arc circles
The idea 2 doesn't seem to work in some case. (see the case with a small and a large arcs)
"follow a circle, which center is the middle of the centers of the two arc circles" (idea 2) doesn't seem to work with a large and a small arcs.
